# Overview

This rule enforces strict modification boundaries and clean code standards.
It must be followed for all code generation and refactoring tasks.

# Scope Control

- Only modify files explicitly mentioned in the task.
- Do NOT refactor unrelated files.
- Do NOT introduce ripple changes across the codebase.
- If a change requires modifying additional files, explicitly state why before doing so.

# Code Style

- Write clean, readable, modular code.
- Do not add comments unless explicitly requested.
- Avoid unnecessary abstractions.
- Follow existing project patterns and naming conventions.
- Do not change formatting style unless required.

# Refactoring Rules

- Do not rename variables, functions, or components unless required.
- Do not reorganize folder structure.
- Do not optimize unless requested.

# Safety

- Do not remove existing functionality.
- Preserve backward compatibility unless explicitly instructed otherwise.
